Each row shows the variation in children's arithmetic levels within a given grade. For example, among children in Std III, 3.4% cannot even recognize numbers 1-9, 17.5% can recognize numbers up to 9 but cannot recognize numbers up to 99 or higher, 47.9% can recognize numbers up to 99 but cannot do subtraction, 25% can do subtraction but cannot do division, and 6.2% can do division. For each grade, the total of these exclusive categories is 100%.

